    "The attack method was evaluated on a collection of masked clinical language models and compared its performance against a baseline approach that completely relies on the loss of the target model, as established in previous works ( [308], [243]).",
    "Some works investigated MIA methods in LMs on specific domains, e.g., clinical language models.",
    "Jagannatha et al.",
    "investigated the risks [103] of training-data leakage to estimate the empirical privacy leaks for model architectures such as BERT [57] and GPT-2 [204].",
    "Kaneko et al."
